  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-04-08",
    "date": "2021-05-07T14:42:45Z",
    "text": "Veterans Fellowship Act\n\nThis bill requires the Veterans' Employment and Training Service within the Department of Labor to implement a pilot program under which states may use grants or contracts to carry out a short-term fellowship program. Each fellowship program must run for a period that does not exceed 20 weeks, provide a monthly stipend, and provide veterans an opportunity to be employed on a long-term basis following the fellowship.\n\nThe Government Accountability Office must report on the pilot program within four years after it commences."
  },
